Afrikaans Language Monument.label: Afrikaans Language Monument
Afrikaans Language Monument.description: The Afrikaans Language Monument is located on a hill overlooking Paarl, Western Cape Province, South Africa. Wikipedia

Mao Zedong Statue (Chengdu).label: Mao Zedong Statue
Mao Zedong Statue (Chengdu).description: The Mao Zedong Statue is located in Tianfu Square, Chengdu, Sichuan, China. The monument stands 30 m tall and depicts Mao Zedong with an outstretched arm. Wikipedia

Ontario Veterans Memorial.label: Ontario Veterans Memorial
Ontario Veterans Memorial.description: Ontario Veterans War Memorial is a 30-metre-long granite wall located on the front south lawn of Queen's Park in Toronto, Ontario. The wall was designed by Allan Harding MacKay and landscape architectural firm Phillips Farevaag Smallenberg. Wikipedia

Cross of All Nations.label: Cross of All Nations
Cross of All Nations.description: The Cross of All Nations is a monumental cross located in Qanat Bakish, a locality close to the Lebanese town of Baskinta. The cross was built near a church dating back to 1898 on a land belonging to the Lebanese Maronite Order. Wikipedia

Clock Tower, Faisalabad.label: Clock Tower
Clock Tower, Faisalabad.description: The Faisalabad Clock Tower is a clock tower in Faisalabad, Punjab, Pakistan, and is one of the oldest monuments still standing in its original state from the period of the British Raj. Wikipedia

Dewey Arch.label: Dewey Arch
Dewey Arch.description: The Dewey Arch was a triumphal arch that stood from 1899 to 1900 at Madison Square in Manhattan, New York. Wikipedia

Yad Kennedy.label: Yad Kennedy
Yad Kennedy.description: Yad Kennedy, located in the Mateh Yehuda Region near Jerusalem, Israel, is a memorial to John F. Kennedy, the 35th President of the United States, who was assassinated in Dallas, Texas in 1963. Wikipedia

Tomb of Sher Shah Suri.label: Tomb of Sher Shah Suri
Tomb of Sher Shah Suri.description: The tomb of Sher Shah Suri is in the Sasaram town of Bihar state, India. The tomb was built in memory of Emperor Sher Shah Suri, a Pathan from Bihar who defeated the Mughal Empire and founded the Suri Empire in northern India. Wikipedia

Emperors Yan and Huang.label: Emperors Yan and Huang
Emperors Yan and Huang.description: The sculptures of the Emperors Yan and Huang are the fifth tallest statues in the world at 106 meters. They depict two of the earliest Chinese emperors, Yan Di and Huang Di. The construction lasted 20 years and was completed in 2007. Wikipedia

Terry Fox Memorial and Lookout.label: Terry Fox Memorial and Lookout
Terry Fox Memorial and Lookout.description: The Terry Fox Monument, situated in the outskirts of Thunder Bay, Ontario, Canada, signifies cancer research activist Terry Fox's tragic halt in his Marathon of Hope on 31 August 1980. Wikipedia

Great Buddha of Thailand.label: Great Buddha of Thailand
Great Buddha of Thailand.description: The Great Buddha of Thailand, also known as The Big Buddha, The Big Buddha of Thailand, Phra Buddha Maha Nawamin, and Mahaminh Sakayamunee Visejchaicharn, is the tallest statue in Thailand, and the ninth tallest in the world. Wikipedia

Prince Henry the Navigator (statue).label: Prince Henry the Navigator
Prince Henry the Navigator (statue).description: Prince Henry the Navigator is an historic statue located on a traffic median at the intersection of Eastern Avenue and Pleasant Street in the Flint Village section of Fall River, Massachusetts. Wikipedia

Marcos Museum and Mausoleum.label: Marcos Museum and Mausoleum
Marcos Museum and Mausoleum.description: The Marcos Museum and Mausoleum integrates both memorabilia storage and the current resting place of Ferdinand Edralin Marcos. It is situated in the heart of Batac City, Ilocos Norte. Wikipedia

Rizal Monument.label: Rizal Monument
Rizal Monument.description: The Rizal Monument originally called the Motto Stella is a memorial monument in Rizal Park in Manila, Philippines built to commemorate the Filipino nationalist, José Rizal. Wikipedia

Sigismund's Column.label: Sigismund's Column
Sigismund's Column.description: Sigismund's Column, erected in 1644, is located in Castle Square, Warsaw, Poland. It is one of Warsaw's most famous landmarks and one of the oldest secular monuments in northern Europe. Wikipedia

Raibania fort.label: Raibania fort
Raibania fort.description: Raibania fort is a group of ancient forts in Baleswar district, Odisha India. This fort complex is considered as the biggest medieval fort of eastern India. It was built during the Buddhist era in Odisha. Wikipedia

African Renaissance Monument.label: African Renaissance Monument
African Renaissance Monument.description: The African Renaissance Monument is a 49m tall bronze statue located on top of one of the twin hills known as Collines des Mamelles, outside of Dakar, Senegal. Wikipedia

Georgia Guidestones.label: Georgia Guidestones
Georgia Guidestones.description: The Georgia Guidestones is a granite monument in Elbert County, Georgia, USA. A message clearly conveying a set of ten guidelines is inscribed on the structure in eight modern languages, and a shorter ... Wikipedia

Matthias Corvinus Monument.label: Matthias Corvinus Monument
Matthias Corvinus Monument.description:
The Matthias Corvinus Monument is a monument in Cluj-Napoca, Romania.
This classified historic monument, conceived by János Fadrusz and opened in 1902, represents Matthias Corvinus. Wikipedia

Yusif ibn Kuseyir Mausoleum.label: Yusif ibn Kuseyir Mausoleum
Yusif ibn Kuseyir Mausoleum.description: The Mausoleum of Yusif ibn Kuseyir was built in 1161–1162, in Nakchivan city. Architect of the mausoleum was Ajami ibn Abubakr Nakhchivani. Wikipedia

Monument aux braves de N.D.G..label: Monument aux braves de N.D.G.
Monument aux braves de N.D.G..description: The Monument aux braves de Notre-Dame-de-Grâce is a monument in Montreal. Wikipedia

Samadhi of Ranjit Singh.label: Samadhi of Ranjit Singh
Samadhi of Ranjit Singh.description: The Samadhi of Ranjit Singh is a building housing the funerary urns of the Sikh ruler Maharaja Ranjit Singh. It is located near the Lahore Fort and Badshahi Mosque in Lahore, Pakistan. Wikipedia

Yar Muhammad Kalhoro.label: Yar Muhammad Kalhoro
Yar Muhammad Kalhoro.description: Mian Yar Muhammad Kalhoro became chieftain of Kalhora clan after his elder brother Mian Din muhammad Kalhoro who was imprisoned and Killed in Multan Jail by Prince Muiz-ud-Din Muhammad, the governor of Multan in 1700 A.D. Wikipedia

National Law Enforcement Officers Memori.label: National Law Enforcement Officers Memorial
National Law Enforcement Officers Memori.description: The National Law Enforcement Officers Memorial in Washington, D.C., at Judiciary Square, honors more than 19,000 U.S. law enforcement officers who have died in the line of duty throughout history. Wikipedia

Commando Memorial.label: Commando Memorial
Commando Memorial.description: The Commando Memorial is a Category A listed monument in Scotland, dedicated to the men of the original British Commando Forces raised during World War II. Wikipedia

Temple of Augustus (Pula).label: Temple of Augustus
Temple of Augustus (Pula).description: The Temple of Augustus is a well-preserved Roman temple in the city of Pula, Croatia. Dedicated to the first Roman emperor, Augustus, it was probably built during the emperor's lifetime at some point between 2 BC and his death in AD 14. Wikipedia

Triumphal arch, Chişinău.label: Triumphal arch, Chişinău
Triumphal arch, Chişinău.description: The Triumphal arch is a monument in Central Chişinău. Wikipedia

Bobby Moore Sculpture.label: Statue of Bobby Moore, Wembley
Bobby Moore Sculpture.description: The Bobby Moore statue is a bronze sculpture of the former West Ham and England footballer Bobby Moore, situated outside England's national stadium, Wembley Stadium, in London. Wikipedia

Nizami Mausoleum.label: Nizami Mausoleum
Nizami Mausoleum.description: The Nizami Mausoleum, built in honor of the 12th-century poet Nizami Ganjavi, stands just outside the city of Ganja, Azerbaijan. Wikipedia

Jam Gadang.label: Jam Gadang

War Memorial of Montreal West.label: War Memorial of Montreal West
War Memorial of Montreal West.description: The War Memorial of Montreal West is a monument in Montreal. Wikipedia

Royal Monastery of Brou.label: Royal Monastery of Brou
Royal Monastery of Brou.description: The Royal Monastery of Brou is a religious complex located at Bourg-en-Bresse in the Ain département, central France. Wikipedia

Hagia Sophia.label: Hagia Sophia
Hagia Sophia.description: Hagia Sophia is a former Greek Orthodox patriarchal basilica, later an imperial mosque, and now a museum in Istanbul, Turkey. Wikipedia

Robert Burns Memorial (Montreal).description: The Robert Burns Memorial is a monument of sculptor G. A. Lawson located at Dorchester Square in Downtown Montreal. Wikipedia
Subject: Robert Burns

Alley of Classics, Bălţi.label: Alley of Classics, Bălţi

Tsar Cannon.description: The Tsar Cannon is a large, 5.94 metres long cannon on display on the grounds of the Moscow Kremlin. It was cast in 1586 in Moscow, by the Russian master bronze caster Andrey Chokhov. Mostly of symbolic impact, it was never used in a war. Wikipedia

Château de Fondat.label: Château de Fondat
Château de Fondat.description: The Château de Fondat is a château in the French commune of Saint-Justin, in Landes, Aquitane, France. Wikipedia

Skanderbeg Monument (Tirana).label: Skanderbeg Monument
Skanderbeg Monument (Tirana).description: The Skanderbeg Monument is a monument located in the Skanderbeg Square, Tirana, Albania. Wikipedia

Petagas War Memorial.label: Petagas War Memorial

Veera Abhaya Anjaneya Hanuman Swami.label: Veera Abhaya Anjaneya Hanuman Swami
Veera Abhaya Anjaneya Hanuman Swami.description: Veera Abhaya Anjaneya Hanuman Swami is a statue in depicting Hanuman. It is located in the village of Paritala, approximately 30 km from the city of Vijayawada, in the state of Andhra Pradesh, India. Wikipedia

Tuhutum Monument.label: Tuhutum Monument
Tuhutum Monument.description: The Tuhutum Monument was an obelisk in Zalău, Romania. Wikipedia

Wesselényi Monument.label: Wesselényi Monument
Wesselényi Monument.description:
The Wesselényi Monument is a monument in Zalău, Romania.

Fermière Monument (Montreal).label: Fermière Monument
Fermière Monument (Montreal).description: La Fermière is a monument in Montreal. Wikipedia

George-Étienne Cartier Monument.label: George-Étienne Cartier Monument
George-Étienne Cartier Monument.description:
The George-Étienne Cartier Monument is a monument in Mount Royal Park to George-Étienne Cartier by sculptor George William Hill.

Macdonald Monument.label: Macdonald Monument

South African War Memorial (Toronto).label: South African War Memorial
South African War Memorial (Toronto).description: The South African War Memorial is a memorial located at University Avenue and Queen Street West in Toronto. Wikipedia

Dante Monument (Montreal).label: Dante Monument
Dante Monument (Montreal).description: The Dante Monument is a memorial in Little Italy, Montreal. Wikipedia

Çanakkale Martyrs' Memorial.label: Çanakkale Martyrs' Memorial
Çanakkale Martyrs' Memorial.description: The Çanakkale Martyrs' Memorial is a war memorial commemorating the service of about 253,000 Turkish soldiers who participated at the Battle of Gallipoli, which took place from April 1915 to December 1915 during the First World War. Wikipedia

Anıtkabir.label: Anıtkabir
Anıtkabir.description: Anıtkabir is the mausoleum of Mustafa Kemal Atatürk, the leader of the Turkish War of Independence and the founder and first President of the Republic of Turkey. Wikipedia

Cenotaph (Montreal).label: Cenotaph
Cenotaph (Montreal).description: The Cenotaph is a public monument in Montreal. Wikipedia

Castillo de San Andrés.label: Castillo de San Andrés
Castillo de San Andrés.description: The Castillo o Torre de San Andrés is located in the village of San Andrés. This castle served to protect the island of Tenerife from pirate attacks. Wikipedia

Harvard Bixi.label: Harvard Bixi
Harvard Bixi.description: The Harvard Bixi is a 17-foot high, 27 ton Chinese marble stele located at Harvard University, north of Boylston Hall and west of Widener Library in Harvard Yard, in Cambridge, Massachusetts. Wikipedia

Atkinson Clock Tower.label: Atkinson Clock Tower

Diri Baba Mausoleum.label: Diri Baba Mausoleum
Diri Baba Mausoleum.description: Diri Baba Mausoleum – is a mausoleum of Sheikh Diri Baba, located in Maraza city of Gobustan Rayon of Azerbaijan. Wikipedia

Roddick Gates.label: Roddick Gates
Roddick Gates.description:
The Roddick Memorial Gates are a monument in Montreal and the main entrance to the McGill University.
The Roddick Gates are on Sherbrooke Street and are at the head of the very short but broad McGill College Avenue which starts at Place Ville-Marie. Wikipedia

Tuba Dei.label: Tuba Dei
Tuba Dei.description: Tuba Dei, is the largest medieval bell in Poland and one of the largest medieval bells in Europe, hanging in the tower of Ss. Johns Cathedral in Toruń. Wikipedia

Wilfrid Laurier Memorial.label: Wilfrid Laurier Memorial
Wilfrid Laurier Memorial.description: The Wilfrid Laurier Memorial is a monument in Downtown Montreal. Wikipedia

Boer War Memorial (Montreal).label: Boer War Memorial
Boer War Memorial (Montreal).description: The Boer War Memorial is a monument of sculptor George W. Hill located at Dorchester Square in Downtown Montreal. Wikipedia

Fort Moore.label: Fort Moore

Choeung Ek.label: Choeung Ek
Choeung Ek.description: Choeung Ek, the site of a former orchard and mass grave of victims of the Khmer Rouge - killed between 1975 and 1979 - about 17 km south of Phnom Penh, Cambodia, is the best-known of the sites known as ... Wikipedia

Monument to Minin and Pozharsky.label: Monument to Minin and Pozharsky
Monument to Minin and Pozharsky.description: The Monument to Minin and Pozharsky is a bronze statue on Red Square in Moscow, Russia, in front of Saint Basil's Cathedral. Wikipedia

John the Baptist Monument.label: John the Baptist Monument
John the Baptist Monument.description: The John the Baptist Monument is a 19.8-meter concrete statue in downtown San Juan de los Morros, Guárico state, Venezuela, erected in honor of John the Baptist. Commonly called San Juanote, it's one of the highest statues in Venezuela. Wikipedia

Pir Khidir Zinda.label: Pir Khidir Zinda
Pir Khidir Zinda.description: Pir Khidir Zinda or Khidir Zunja – is a sacred place for Muslims, located at the foot of Beshbarmag rock in Siyazan rayon of Azerbaijan. Wikipedia

Arch of the Sergii.label: Arch of the Sergii
Arch of the Sergii.description: Arch of the Sergii is an Ancient Roman triumphal arch located in Pula, Croatia. The arch commemorates three brothers of the Sergii family, specifically Lucius Sergius Lepidus, a tribune serving in the ... Wikipedia

Martin Luther King, Jr. Memorial.label: Martin Luther King, Jr. Memorial
Martin Luther King, Jr. Memorial.description: The Martin Luther King, Jr. Memorial is located in West Potomac Park in Washington, D.C., southwest of the National Mall. The national memorial is America's 395th unit in the national park service. Wikipedia

Sheykh Babi Yagub Mausoleum.label: Sheykh Babi Yagub Mausoleum
Sheykh Babi Yagub Mausoleum.description: Sheykh Babi Yagub Mausoleum – is a mausoleum in Babi village of Fuzuli Rayon of Azerbaijan and was built in 1272. Wikipedia

Voortrekker Monument.label: Voortrekker Monument
Voortrekker Monument.description: The Voortrekker Monument is located just south of Pretoria in South Africa. This massive granite structure is prominently located on a hilltop, and was raised to commemorate the Voortrekkers who left the Cape Colony between 1835 and 1854. Wikipedia

Alexander I Statue in Taganrog.label: Alexander I Statue in Taganrog
Alexander I Statue in Taganrog.description: The monument to Alexander I of Russia was erected on the initiative of the people of Taganrog in memory of the emperor's stay and death in the city. Wikipedia

Garibaldi Monument in Taganrog.label: Garibaldi Monument in Taganrog
Garibaldi Monument in Taganrog.description: In the first half of 19th century Taganrog was one of the largest ports in Russia. Hundreds of ships from European ports came into the haven. Wikipedia

Red Basilica.label: Red Basilica
Red Basilica.description: The "Red Basilica", also called variously the Red Hall and Red Courtyard, is a monumental ruined temple in the ancient city of Pergamon, now Bergama, in western Turkey. Wikipedia

Liberty Bell.label: Liberty Bell
Liberty Bell.description: The Liberty Bell is an iconic symbol of American independence, located in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. Wikipedia

Grand Bazaar, Istanbul.label: Grand Bazaar
Grand Bazaar, Istanbul.description: The Grand Bazaar in Istanbul is one of the largest and oldest covered markets in the world, with 61 covered streets and over 3,000 shops which attract between 250,000 and 400,000 visitors daily. Wikipedia

Samora Machel Monument.label: Samora Machel Monument

Tağlar Cave.label: Tağlar Cave

National Monument (Amsterdam).description: The National Monument is a 1956 World War II monument on Dam Square in Amsterdam. A national Remembrance of the Dead ceremony is held at the monument every year on 4 May to commemorate the casualties of World War II and subsequent armed conflicts. Wikipedia

Ranevskaya Monument.label: Ranevskaya Monument
Ranevskaya Monument.description:
The Monument to Faina Ranevskaya, designed and sculpted by David Begalov is located in front of Faina Ranevskaya's birth house in Taganrog.
